parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can lead to the seat belt not retracting properly, which can cause the seat belt to become loose or disengaged, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt does not retract
the seat belt retractor makes a clicking sound but does not retract
the seat belt becomes loose or disengaged
the seat belt warning light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent malfunction of the seat belt can cause the seat belt to retract and release unexpectedly, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The seat belt retracts and releases on its own
the seat belt retractor makes a clicking sound intermittently
the seat belt becomes loose or disengaged unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can cause the seat belt to become loose or disengaged, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle breaks or becomes loose
the seat belt buckle push button breaks
the seat belt buckle comes loose during impact.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Recall Issues with Seat Belt Repairs
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of dealerships to properly repair or replace seat belts under recall can lead to continued safety risks for vehicle occupants.
symptoms: Dealerships refuse to accept recall notices
dealerships do not have parts available to correct recall
dealerships charge extra for parts not included in recall notice.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or stalls when shifting gears
the transmission slips or jerks
the transmission makes unusual noises
the vehicle loses power or acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the odometer cable can cause the odometer to stop working, leading to inaccurate mileage readings and potential issues with vehicle maintenance and resale value.
symptoms: The odometer stops working
the odometer reading is inaccurate
the odometer cable is broken or damaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the CV boot can cause the CV joint to wear out prematurely, leading to vibrations, noise, and potentially causing the vehicle to lose power or stall.
symptoms: The vehicle vibrates or shakes
the CV joint makes unusual noises
the CV boot is cracked or broken.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause the vehicle to suddenly and unexpectedly speed up, leading to accidents, loss of control, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates without input from the driver
the accelerator pedal sticks
the vehicle idles excessively
the RPMs increase unexpectedly
the vehicle surges forward.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A stuck accelerator pedal can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to accidents, loss of control, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal feels stuck or stuck to the floor
the vehicle accelerates without input from the driver
the vehicle surges forward.
